body: grpc:// debug URL implementation has two parts: client (debug ops) and server. The server part, which is defined as a Python grpc library, is currently not available in open source. See b/23796275 cited below. So even though the client side has been available in OSS for a while, OSS users haven't been able to use the feature yet to the lack of a working server side. As such, the change here shouldn't affect them.
